Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State has tested negative to Coronavirus.
The governor announced on Thursday via his twitter handle that the result of the test conducted came out negative.
Akeredolu said he received a text message from the state Commissioner for Health, Dr. Wahab Adegbenro, stating his COVID-19 status
In his tweet, Akeredolu said, “I just received the above text from the Commissioner for Health regarding my #Covid19 test results. We give all glory to God. Wish everyone affected speedy recovery.”
The  Commissioner for Information, Donald Ojogo Ojogo, also confirmed the result in a statement,  saying  Governor Akeredolu willingly offered to be tested on Wednesday morning after one of his earlier contacts had been confirmed to be positive.

			
